   <ul class="ksps table_list">
    <li>
     <div class="grid_wrapper">
      <div class="grid_6_enh_4 copy">
       <h2>Your website is how you’re seen</h2>
       <p>First impressions last forever: your website must not only <em>showcase your talent</em>, it should also show that you’re a <em>trustworthy professional who cares.</em> Both are at the core of our promise.</p>
       <p>A PhotoDeck website will let your clients fully enjoy your work in its fullscreen glory, without distracting gimmicks, and without compromising a functional and pleasing user experience — even in advanced <a href="http://www.photodeck.com/tour/#proofing">proofing</a> or <a href="http://www.photodeck.com/tour/#ecommerce">ecommerce</a> environments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid_3_enh_15 push_half with_illustrations enhanced"> 
       <img src="http://w3assets.photodeck.com/wp-content/uploads/homepage/displays.svg" class="illustration">
      </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
     </div></li>
    <li>
     <div class="grid_wrapper">
      <p class="testimonial-quote">A client this week were so impressed by the facilities offered on my website for them to download images that they offered me the job there and then. // <b>Andrew Chamberlain, architectural photographer</b></p>
     </div></li>
    <li>
     <div class="grid_wrapper" style="position:relative">
      <div class="grid_6_enh_4 copy">
       <h2>Your clients love speed</h2>
       <p>Whether it is to <em>hire you</em>, to <em>download a job</em>, or to <em>purchase images or videos</em>, the faster your website is, the more likely clients will do business with you. That’s why we’ve built <a href="http://www.photodeck.com/tour/#speed">the fastest photography websites around</a>.</p>
       <p>Naturally, all PhotoDeck sites work <em>beautifully on any device.</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid_3_enh_15 push_half with_illustrations enhanced"> 
       <img src="http://w3assets.photodeck.com/wp-content/uploads/homepage/speedmeter_bw.svg" class="illustration" style="width: 100px ">
      </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
     </div></li>
    <li>
     <div class="grid_wrapper">
      <div class="grid_6_enh_4 copy">
       <h2>Providers taking a cut off your sales?</h2>
       <p>Let’s be honest. The role of a website provider is to give you a tool to connect your clients to your work — and make their purchase as easy as possible. You’re the one doing the selling. So why would we take commissions?</p>
       <p><em>We don’t.</em> We earn our living only by providing you the best possible website and tools to run your business online more successfully. That, in our view, is fair. Learn more <a href="http://www.photodeck.com/about/">about us&nbsp;›</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid_3_enh_15 push_half with_illustrations enhanced"> 
       <img src="http://w3assets.photodeck.com/wp-content/uploads/homepage/no_commission.svg" class="illustration">
      </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
     </div></li>
    <li class="country_FR country_FI country_ES country_DE country_DK country_BR country_PT country_RU country_NO country_NL country_IT country_TR country_CH" style="display:none;">
     <div class="grid_wrapper">
      <div class="grid_6_enh_4 copy">
       <h2 class="localization">English for your <span class="country_FR" style="display:none;">French</span> <span class="country_FI" style="display:none;">Finnish</span> <span class="country_ES" style="display:none;">Spanish</span> <span class="country_DE" style="display:none;">German</span> <span class="country_DK" style="display:none;">Danish</span> <span class="country_BR" style="display:none;">Brazilian</span> <span class="country_PT" style="display:none;">Portuguese</span> <span class="country_RU" style="display:none;">Russian</span> <span class="country_NO" style="display:none;">Norwegian</span> <span class="country_NL" style="display:none;">Dutch</span> <span class="country_IT" style="display:none;">Italian</span> <span class="country_TR" style="display:none;">Turkish</span> <span class="country_CH" style="display:none;">Swiss</span> <span class="country_rescue">French</span> clients?</h2>
       <p>No way. With PhotoDeck, your clients can enjoy your website powerhouse <a href="http://www.photodeck.com/language/">in their own language</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid_3_enh_15 push_half with_illustrations enhanced"></div>
